{{Infobox organization |name = Geological Survey of Bangladesh |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1971 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.gsb.gov.bd/ Geological Survey of Bangladesh] |remarks = }}
'''Geological Survey of Bangladesh''' or GSB is an autonomous national organization working in Geo-scientific activities in Bangladesh and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="rds">{{cite web|last1=Rahman|first1=QM Arifur|title=Geological Survey of Bangladesh|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Geological_Survey_of_Bangladesh|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=4 February 2017|language=en}}</ref> The incumbent Director General of Geological Survey of Bangladesh is Kazi Jebunnesa Begum.<ref>{{cite web|title=অফিস আদেশ|trans-title=Office order|url=http://www.gsb.gov.bd/rvedr$/images/files/new%20dg-K%20Zebunnesa%20begum%20160117.jpg|website=gsb.gov.bd|publisher= Energy and Mineral Resources Division |accessdate=2 April 2017}}</ref>
==History== The Geological Survey of Bangladesh was founded in 1971 immediately after the Independence of Bangladesh. The organization was formed out of the remnaints of Geological Survey of Pakistan in East Pakistan. The [[Geological Survey of Pakistan]] traces its origins to the [[Geological Survey of India]] which was founded in 1836.<ref name="rds"></ref> The agency is run by the [[Ministry of Power, Energy and Mineral Resources|Ministry of Mineral Resources]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Geological Survey of Bangladesh to drill in Naogaon|url=http://bdnews24.com/economy/2016/02/05/geological-survey-of-bangladesh-to-drill-in-naogaon|website=bdnews24.com|accessdate=4 February 2017}}</ref> It has discovered a number of mines in Bangladesh.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Coal|title=Coal - Banglapedia|website=en.banglapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2017-02-04}}</ref>
