{{Infobox Protected area | name = Moscos Islands Wildlife Sanctuary | iucn_category = IV | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Burma | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within Burma | map_width = | location ={{flag|Burma}} | nearest_city = [[Yebyu]] and [[Launglon]] | coordinates = {{coord|14|07|30|N|97|48|15|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = 49.19 km² | established = 1927 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = Burma Forest Department }} The '''Moscos Islands Wildlife Sanctuary''' is a demarcated wildlife reserve located in the [[Moscos Islands]], [[Burma]]. It is governed by the Burma Forest Department and the level of protection is total.
The main purposes of the reserve are [[habitat conservation]] and [[natural resources]] maintenance. The typical habitat is [[tropical evergreen forest]]. Tourists are not allowed within the wildlife reserve.<ref>[http://www.banca-env.org/ebook.pdf Myanmar Protected Areas - Context, Current Status and Challenges] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120417063155/http://www.banca-env.org/ebook.pdf |date=2012-04-17 }}</ref>
