{{Coord|7|20|36.0|N|134|28|05.5|E|display=title}} {{Infobox venue | name = Ngarachamayong Culture Center | nickname = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Ngarachamayong Culture Center.JPG | image_size = 250px | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | address = | location = [[Koror]], [[Palau]] | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | type = [[Cultural center]] | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
The '''Ngarachamayong Culture Center''' is a [[cultural center]] in [[Koror]], [[Palau]].
==History== The idea for the establishment of the cultural center originated when a group of visionary women held a special meeting to discuss ways of preserving the culture and tradition of the Palauan people. The meeting led to the establishment of a series of Mechesil Belau Conferences. During these conferences the idea to establish a cultural center was born. Subsequently, the Ngarachamayong, Inc. was incorporated. The cultural center was then constructed with funding from the [[Politics of Palau|Government of Palau]] and the [[Government of the Republic of China]].<ref name="oceanislandtravel.com">{{cite web|url=http://oceanislandtravel.com/home.asp?aid=136|title=Ngarachamayong Culture Center|website=Ocean Island Travel|accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The cultural center exhibits the people and culture of the Palauan people.<ref name="oceanislandtravel.com"/>
